verses.text: Now these \add are\add* the generations of Esau , who \add is\add* Edom.
Esau took his wives of the daughters of Canaan ; Adah the daughter of Elon the Hittite , and Aholibamah the daughter of Anah the daughter of Zibeon the Hivite ;
And Bashemath Ishmael’s daughter , sister of Nebajoth.\f + \fr 36.3 \ft Bashemath: or, Mahalath\f*
And Adah bare to Esau Eliphaz ; and Bashemath bare Reuel ;
And Aholibamah bare Jeush , and Jaalam , and Korah : these \add are\add* the sons of Esau , which were born unto him in the land of Canaan.

And Esau took his wives , and his sons , and his daughters , and all the persons of his house , and his cattle , and all his beasts , and all his substance , which he had got in the land of Canaan ; and went into the country from the face of his brother Jacob.\f + \fr 36.6 \ft persons: Heb. souls\f*
For their riches were more than that they might dwell together ; and the land wherein they were strangers could not bear them because of their cattle.
Thus dwelt Esau in mount Seir : Esau \add is\add* Edom. \p
¶ And these \add are\add* the generations of Esau the father of the Edomites in mount Seir :\f + \fr 36.9 \ft the Edomites: Heb. Edom\f*
These \add are\add* the names of Esau’s sons ; Eliphaz the son of Adah the wife of Esau , Reuel the son of Bashemath the wife of Esau.
And the sons of Eliphaz were Teman , Omar , Zepho , and Gatam , and Kenaz.\f + \fr 36.11 \ft Zepho: or, Zephi\f*
And Timna was concubine to Eliphaz Esau’s son ; and she bare to Eliphaz Amalek : these \add were\add* the sons of Adah Esau’s wife.
And these \add are\add* the sons of Reuel ; Nahath , and Zerah , Shammah , and Mizzah : these were the sons of Bashemath Esau’s wife. \p
¶ And these were the sons of Aholibamah , the daughter of Anah the daughter of Zibeon , Esau’s wife : and she bare to Esau Jeush , and Jaalam , and Korah. \p
¶ These \add were\add* dukes of the sons of Esau : the sons of Eliphaz the firstborn \add son\add* of Esau ; duke Teman , duke Omar , duke Zepho , duke Kenaz ,
Duke Korah , duke Gatam , \add and\add* duke Amalek : these \add are\add* the dukes \add that came\add* of Eliphaz in the land of Edom ; these \add were\add* the sons of Adah. \p

¶ And these \add are\add* the sons of Reuel Esau’s son ; duke Nahath , duke Zerah , duke Shammah , duke Mizzah : these \add are\add* the dukes \add that came\add* of Reuel in the land of Edom ; these \add are\add* the sons of Bashemath Esau’s wife. \p

¶ And these \add are\add* the sons of Aholibamah Esau’s wife ; duke Jeush , duke Jaalam , duke Korah : these \add were\add* the dukes \add that came\add* of Aholibamah the daughter of Anah , Esau’s wife.
These \add are\add* the sons of Esau , who \add is\add* Edom , and these \add are\add* their dukes. \p
¶ These \add are\add* the sons of Seir the Horite , who inhabited the land ; Lotan , and Shobal , and Zibeon , and Anah ,
And Dishon , and Ezer , and Dishan : these \add are\add* the dukes of the Horites , the children of Seir in the land of Edom.
And the children of Lotan were Hori and Hemam ; and Lotan’s sister \add was\add* Timna.\f + \fr 36.22 \ft Hemam: or, Homam\f*
And the children of Shobal \add were\add* these; Alvan , and Manahath , and Ebal , Shepho , and Onam.\f + \fr 36.23 \ft Alvan: or, Alian\f*\f + \fr 36.23 \ft Shepho: or, Shephi\f*
And these \add are\add* the children of Zibeon ; both Ajah , and Anah : this \add was that\add* Anah that found the mules in the wilderness , as he fed the asses of Zibeon his father.
And the children of Anah \add were\add* these; Dishon , and Aholibamah the daughter of Anah.
And these \add are\add* the children of Dishon ; Hemdan , and Eshban , and Ithran , and Cheran.\f + \fr 36.26 \ft Hemdan: or, Amram\f*
The children of Ezer \add are\add* these; Bilhan , and Zaavan , and Akan.\f + \fr 36.27 \ft Akan: or, Jakan\f*
The children of Dishan \add are\add* these; Uz , and Aran.
These \add are\add* the dukes \add that came\add* of the Horites ; duke Lotan , duke Shobal , duke Zibeon , duke Anah ,
Duke Dishon , duke Ezer , duke Dishan : these \add are\add* the dukes \add that came\add* of Hori , among their dukes in the land of Seir. \p
¶ And these \add are\add* the kings that reigned in the land of Edom , before there reigned any king over the children of Israel.
And Bela the son of Beor reigned in Edom : and the name of his city \add was\add* Dinhabah.
And Bela died , and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his stead.
And Jobab died , and Husham of the land of Temani reigned in his stead.
And Husham died , and Hadad the son of Bedad , who smote Midian in the field of Moab , reigned in his stead: and the name of his city \add was\add* Avith.
And Hadad died , and Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his stead.
And Samlah died , and Saul of Rehoboth \add by\add* the river reigned in his stead.
And Saul died , and Baal-hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his stead.

And Baal-hanan the son of Achbor died , and Hadar reigned in his stead: and the name of his city \add was\add* Pau ; and his wife’s name \add was\add* Mehetabel , the daughter of Matred , the daughter of Mezahab.\f + \fr 36.39 \ft Hadar, Pau: or, Hadad, Pai: after his death was an Aristocracy\f*

And these \add are\add* the names of the dukes \add that came\add* of Esau , according to their families , after their places , by their names ; duke Timnah , duke Alvah , duke Jetheth ,\f + \fr 36.40 \ft Alvah: or, Aliah\f*
Duke Aholibamah , duke Elah , duke Pinon ,
Duke Kenaz , duke Teman , duke Mibzar ,

Duke Magdiel , duke Iram : these \add be\add* the dukes of Edom , according to their habitations in the land of their possession : he \add is\add* Esau the father of the Edomites.\f + \fr 36.43 \ft the Edomites: Heb. Edom\f*
